<span id="freeTextContainer17574648754693106977">I liked it, ended up reading it in one sitting. <br/><br/>The book opens with Ashlyn moving back to her hometown after her husband passes away <a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[I kept wondering why it took her a year to move back to California. What did she do during that year and wouldn&apos;t she have moved home right after her husband died? I also think after a year, she would have been a little further along in her recovery, but I guess everyone is different and it&apos;s not something you just &quot;get over&quot;. <a class='jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction'>(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>. She&apos;s </span>
